commit.title: [mailmap] Update "anonymous" accounts.
commit.message:
[mailmap] Update "anonymous" accounts.

Out of the three "anonymous accounts" one ("coq") has a total of 636 commits
over many years (2000-07-19 to 2006-03-05) and is likely to correspond to
commits from multiple authors, thus it is a true "anonymous" account while:

- the second one ("no author") is actually responsible for a single commit
  (9380f25, the first one ever) whose commit message is "New repository
  initialized by cvs2svn", thus I am renaming this committer to "csv2svn"
  instead of a plain "anonymous";
- the third one is "serpyc" and has also a single commit (88909c9, "Removal of
  trailing spaces", in 2009). Searching "serpyc" in Google gives results on
  gforge (apparently this was a member of the Coq project named G. Serpyc) and
  on coq-contribs (so they did other commits outside of Coq stricto sensu), thus
  I think mailmap should not classify this user as anonymous (we don't do this
  either for GitHub users using pseudonyms).
